==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sleek
<hw>Sleek</hw> <pr>(sl⟦emac⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos> <adjf>Sleeker</adjf>
<pr>(sl⟦emac⟧k"⟦etil⟧r)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Sleekest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>slik</ets>; akin to
Icel. <ets>sl⟦imac⟧kr</ets>, and OE. <ets>sliken</ets> to glide, slide,
G. <ets>schleichen</ets>, OHG. <ets>sl⟦imac⟧hhan</ets>, D.
<ets>slik</ets>, <ets>slijk</ets>, mud, slime, and E. <ets>slink</ets>.
Cf. <er>Slick</er>, <er>Slink</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having an
even, smooth surface; smooth; hence, glossy; <as>as, <ex>sleek</ex>
hair</as>.</def> <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>sleek</qex> her skin, so faultless was her make.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not rough or harsh.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Those rugged names to our like mouths grow <qex>sleek</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sleek
<hw>Sleek</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>With ease and dexterity.</def>
<mark>[Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Sleek
<hw>Sleek</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That which makes smooth;
varnish.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slick.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleek</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Sleek
<hw>Sleek</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Sleeked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>;<pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Sleeking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To make even and smooth; to
render smooth, soft, and glossy; to smooth over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sleeking</qex> her soft alluring locks.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gentle, my lord, <qex>sleek</qex> o'er your rugged looks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sleekly</ent>⟦br⟧
